            "last_activity_date": 1327375969,
            "creation_date": 1327375969,
            "body": "<p><code>%-5s<\/code> means \"a string, left-aligned in a column of at least five characters\", or if you prefer, \"a string, right-padded with spaces until it's at least five characters long\".<\/p>\n\n<p><code>%5s<\/code> is the same, but right-aligned instead of left-aligned (i.e., left-padded instead of right-padded).<\/p>\n\n<p><code>%-15s<\/code> and <code>%15s<\/code>, as you'd expect, are for fifteen-character columns instead of five.<\/p>\n\n<p>For more information on the syntax of format strings, see <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/Formatter.html#syntax\" rel=\"noreferrer\">http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/Formatter.html#syntax<\/a>.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 8981698,
            "question_id": 8981649
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/00a3da01cf3eef469d5880bd7ef680ed?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
